// CANONICAL TEMPLATE — anima multi-objective (Ψ-physics) trainer spine
//
// Resolves Ask 2 of archive/patches/flame-anima-multi-objective-3b-pytorch-
// benchmark-and-stdlib-template.md (filed by anima 2026-05-21):
//   - dual output heads (head_a, head_g) sharing the final embedding
//   - composite loss recipe L = L_ce + λ_ψ·L_psi + λ_phi·L_phi
//     (L_route deferred — see "Honest scope" §C2)
//   - backward via ag_tape over (head_a, head_g, block params, tok_emb)
//   - Mac smoke tier: d=192 L=2 (simplified body — see §C1)
//
// PATH B (ag_tape) implementation. anima downstream is expected to
// clone this template into HEXAD/FLAME/<state-dir>/ and extend the
// body (more layers, real GQA attention, RoPE) for the d=768 single-
// GPU and d=3072 H100 3B tiers. The multi-objective composition
// proven here (dual ag_lmhead + ag_seed_grad + ag_backward_reg) is the
// invariant API contract.
//
// FALSIFIERS:
//   F-MULTIOBJ-MAC-SMOKE-BUILDS         parse + clang clean
//                                        (under HEXA_MAC_BUILD_OK=1)
//   F-MULTIOBJ-BACKWARD-ALL-PARAMS-NONZERO
//                                        ||grad[θ]||₁ > 0 for every
//                                        param ∈ {zT_a, zT_g, W1, W2,
//                                        g1, g2, gF, tok_emb}; both
//                                        heads' loss paths contribute
//                                        to shared params.
//   F-MULTIOBJ-COMBINED-LOSS-DESCENDS    SGD step (lr=0.1) over 5 iters:
//                                        L_total[0] > L_total[4]
//                                        (descent through the composite
//                                        scalar, proves seeds compose).
//
// Honest scope:
//   §C1  Body simplified to L=2 stacked rmsnorm+linear+residual blocks
//        (no GQA attention, no RoPE, no SwiGLU). Mac smoke tier is
//        for spine verification of the multi-objective composition —
//        the FULL transformer body (matching conscious_decoder.py at
//        d=192/d=768/d=3072) is downstream wiring. anima clones this
//        template and substitutes _mini_block_fwd → full
//        decoder_block_lib calls.
//   §C2  L_route deferred. Requires per-layer activation L2/CV taps
//        from inside the ag_tape body. anima's
//        nn_decoder_fwd_with_readout (decoder_lib.hexa:550) exposes
//        a single-position residual hook; per-layer-tension readout
//        is a separate flame extension (track via inbox patch
//        "flame-per-layer-tension-readout" if Ask 3 chooses Path B
//        for 3B).
//   §C3  Numerical parity vs PyTorch eager (F-MULTIOBJ-NUMERICAL-
//        PARITY-PYT) deferred — requires a PyTorch reference run on
//        identical RNG-seeded init. Path: anima fires
//        conscious_decoder.py at d=192 L=2 byte-LM mode (same seeds),
//        compares loss[step=0..4] within ε=1e-4. Not in this template.
//   §C4  3B-FITS-H100-80GB (F-MULTIOBJ-3B-FITS-H100-80GB) deferred —
//        the d=3072 L=28 dispatch is cost-bearing GPU fire territory
//        (Ψ-grid via dancinlab/anima HEXAD/UNCLASSIFIED dispatch).
//
// CROSS-LINK:
//   - archive/patches/flame-anima-multi-objective-3b-pytorch-benchmark-
//     and-stdlib-template.md  (this patch)
//   - archive/patches/flame-anima-dual-head-multiobjective.md  (sibling)
//   - archive/patches/stdlib-print-float-emits-type-tag-not-value.md
//     (CLOSED 2026-05-21 — println(float) now emits actual values via
//      runtime.c cycle 56 hxlcl_vsnprintf %g/%f/%e real impl)
//   - dancinlab/anima conscious_decoder.py (reference for L_ce + L_psi +
//     L_phi formulas)
//   - flame_ag_tape_test.hexa  (single-head ag_tape pattern, Phase 2
//      F-RFC043-AGTAPE-CHAIN-EQ oracle)
